# Helm subchart tarballs are VENDORED (committed), not ignored.
#
# They used to be ignored here and pulled by `helm dependency update`. That
# broke every git-sourced deploy (Argo/Flux/Harness/`git clone && helm install`):
# the clone has no charts/ dir, so helm aborts with
#   "found in Chart.yaml, but missing in charts/ directory: postgresql, redis,
#    opensearch"
# …and the bundled Postgres/Redis/OpenSearch simply never exist.
#
# Vendoring also pins us against Bitnami culling old chart versions from
# oci://registry-1.docker.io/bitnamicharts — a `helm dependency build` of the
# versions in Chart.lock is not guaranteed to resolve any more. ~290KB total.
# Refresh deliberately: `helm dependency update infra/helm/ragdoll` + commit.

# Scratch spike for the connect-rpc transport investigation (not part of
